---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Personalized Medical Marijuana Treatment Plans | Releaf MD" 
  description="Discover how Releaf MD designs custom medical cannabis treatment plans, providing dosing guidelines and clinical support for Florida patients."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-brand-mint py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-brand-primary/10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center space-y-4">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-brand-primary/10 text-brand-primary rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
        🌱 Patient Education
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark leading-tight uppercase">Personalized Medical Marijuana Treatment Plans</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        We don't believe in one-size-fits-all medicine. Learn how we craft custom cannabinoid guidelines tailored to your health goals.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-primary/10 rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-whisper prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">Our Clinical Approach to Cannabis Education</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Many medical marijuana clinics in Florida simply write standard certifications and send patients to the dispensary with zero guidance. At Releaf MD, Dr. Kelly Ennix King takes a different approach. We design a <strong>personalized medical marijuana treatment plan</strong> for every patient, giving you the knowledge and confidence to make informed decisions at the dispensary counter.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">How We Build Your Custom Treatment Plan</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          During your clinical evaluation, Dr. Kelly reviews your medical history, current symptoms, and tolerance levels. We then build a plan that outlines:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-3 text-slate-600 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Cannabinoid Ratios:</strong> The ideal balance of THC, CBD, and minor cannabinoids (like CBG or CBN) for your specific conditions. For example, high-CBD ratios are excellent for daytime inflammation without impairment, while indica-dominant THC profiles are suited for nighttime sleep.</li>
          <li><strong>Administration Methods:</strong> Recommending the safest routes of administration, including sublingual tinctures, oral capsules, topical creams, inhalation (vaping/flower), and transdermal patches.</li>
          <li><strong>Dosing Frequency:</strong> Establishing a clear "start low and go slow" schedule to minimize potential side effects and avoid developing unnecessary tolerance.</li>
          <li><strong>Terpene Profiles:</strong> Explaining how specific aromatic compounds in the cannabis plant (such as Myrcene, Linalool, or Limonene) interact with cannabinoids to create therapeutic effects.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-brand-dark mb-2">Evaluations Include Custom Plans</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">
            All initial consultations and renewal sessions automatically include our comprehensive clinical treatment plan at no extra cost. Book your <a href="/evaluations" class="text-brand-accent font-bold hover:underline">New Patient Evaluation</a> or check our <a href="/renewals" class="text-brand-accent font-bold hover:underline">Renewal Options</a> to begin.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">Tracking and Refining Your Progress</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Your body's endocannabinoid system is unique. What works for one patient may require adjustments for another. We provide education on keeping a symptom journal and tracking your outcomes. When you return for your 30-week physician follow-up, we review your progress and modify your dosage recommendations to maximize clinical results.
        </p>

        <div class="border-t border-slate-100 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 italic">
            Read our <a href="/florida-medical-marijuana-card-guide" class="text-brand-primary font-bold hover:underline">Complete Florida Card Guide</a>.
          </p>
          <a href="/#lead-form" class="bg-brand-accent hover:bg-brand-primary text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-xs uppercase transition-colors shadow-md active-press">
            Schedule Assessment
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
